## 11. Encryption

### Settings Encryption (AES-256-GCM)

Sensitive settings (tokens, passwords) are encrypted at rest in the database:

```
SETTINGS_ENCRYPTION_KEY=<64 hex characters (32 bytes)>
```

How it works:
- `isSensitiveKey(key)` checks if key contains: `token`, `pass`, `secret`, `key`, `webhook`
- On save: `encryptValue(plaintext)` produces `enc:<iv>:<tag>:<ciphertext>` (base64)
- On read: `decryptValue(stored)` detects `enc:` prefix and decrypts
- Without `SETTINGS_ENCRYPTION_KEY`: values stored/returned as plaintext (graceful degradation)

### Key Management

- Generate: `openssl rand -hex 32`
- Store in K8s Secret, not ConfigMap
- All replicas must use the same key
- Key rotation: re-encrypt all values after key change

